rs talk and men magically grow into giants, a Hindu princess falls in love with a Muslim holy man, and goddesses rub shoulders with kings and merchants. Across religion, class, and gender, what binds these fabulous stories together is the characters’ pursuit of living honorably and morally in a difficult, corrupt world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBengali (South Asian people)xFolklore. 0aTaleszIndiazBengal. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023 Englishz978311131918608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023z9783111318264oZDB-23-DSP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079134140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520388949?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520388949423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520388949/original  a978-3-11-079134-1  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131918-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_EMB  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-DSPb2023